@startuml adr001_event_driven
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor #EEF3FF
  BorderColor #1E50A0
  FontColor #1E50A0
}
skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #FFF8E1
  BorderColor #B8860B
  FontColor #333333
}
skinparam arrow {
  Color #1E50A0
  FontColor #333333
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFFDE7
  BorderColor #B8860B
}

title ADR-001: Event-Driven Disruption Detection Pipeline

package "External Sources" {
  [Flight Tracking API] as FlightAPI
  [Weather Alert API] as WeatherAPI
}

package "WanderSync Backend" {
  [Disruption Detection Service] as DDS
  database "Event Log" as EventLog
  [Message Broker\n(Redis Pub/Sub)] as Broker
  [Itinerary Management Service] as IMS
}

FlightAPI --> DDS : webhook / poll (HTTPS)
WeatherAPI --> DDS : webhook / poll (HTTPS)

DDS --> EventLog : persist DisruptionEvent\n(for 85% accuracy audit)
DDS --> Broker   : publish DisruptionEvent

note right of Broker : topic: disruptions

Broker --> IMS : fan-out — update affected bookings\n+ deliver user notification

note bottom of DDS
  Publishes:
  { bookingId, severity,
    alternatives[], timestamp }
end note

note right of IMS
  Single consumer per task1 subsystem design.
  Marks affected bookings and triggers
  user-facing notification delivery.
end note
@enduml
